post_content: Frontier Bowmen is a well-established archery club in Regina offering both indoor and outdoor facilities. The indoor range is located at 2255 14th Avenue with 24/7 member access. The outdoor range at Botkin's Pits features field and 3D courses north of the city.
business_hours: 24/7 member access (indoor restricted Tue/Wed 6-9PM during JOP season)

post_content: Wascana Archers is a nonprofit, 100% volunteer-operated archery club in the Regina area. They operate an indoor range at 109 Hodsman Road and a 60-acre outdoor range approximately 25 km north of Regina with 24/7 member access, trails, and open fields.

The Saskatoon Straight Shooters Archery Club is a family-friendly, inclusive club affiliated with the SAA. They use the Saskatoon Wildlife Federation's 7,000+ sq ft indoor range from October to April and an outdoor range at SWF from May onwards. They also have Tri-Club outdoor range access near Vanscoy.

Bowbusters Archery Club in Vanscoy offers indoor and outdoor archery ranges with 24/7 access for members. Annual club membership is $175 plus a $50 SAA membership. Non-members may shoot as guests up to two times under SAA insurance rules.

Battle River Archers is an active archery club based in Battleford, Saskatchewan. Adult members enjoy 24/7 range access. JOP and Intro to Archery programs run on Tuesdays 6-7:30 PM and Wednesdays 7-9 PM, during which the range is reserved for youth programming.

Thunderhead Archers, established in 1988, operates both an indoor target range (November to April) and an outdoor range (May to October) near Delisle, Saskatchewan. The outdoor range is located east of Delisle off Highway 766.

Thunder Creek Archery Club is a community archery club located in the Town 'N' Country Mall in Moose Jaw, Saskatchewan. They host indoor shooting sessions and are affiliated with the Saskatchewan Archery Association.

Timberland Bow Benders is an archery club based in Prince Albert, Saskatchewan, operating out of the Prince Albert Wildlife Federation grounds on Central Avenue North. The club offers programs and range access for archers of all levels.

Estevan Archery Club offers both indoor and outdoor archery facilities south of Estevan on Highway 47. The outdoor range extends west on Highway 18 towards the boundary dams. The club is affiliated with the Saskatchewan Archery Association.

Swift Current Archery Club holds shooting sessions at the Colonel Clifton Centre in Swift Current, Saskatchewan. The club is affiliated with the Saskatchewan Archery Association and welcomes archers of all skill levels.

Lloydminster & Area Archers operates a versatile facility 15 km east of Lloydminster at the Lloydminster Fish & Game Youth Center. The heated, well-lit indoor range accommodates up to 18 archers at distances up to 40 yards. Outdoor facilities include a FITA range (10-50m) and a Field & 3D course.

No.1 Archery & Sports is a commercial indoor archery range and pro shop established in 1966, located approximately 10 km east of Regina on Highway 1 East. They distribute archery supplies and offer an automated indoor shooting range.
Antler River Archery Club is a community archery club based in Carievale, Saskatchewan, affiliated with the Saskatchewan Archery Association.
Apple Shot Archers Inc is an archery club based in Macoun, Saskatchewan, affiliated with the Saskatchewan Archery Association.
Assiniboine River Archery Club is a community archery club based in Canora, Saskatchewan, affiliated with the Saskatchewan Archery Association.
